    {
      "title": "Quarry Bastion",
      "art": "siege",
      "lines": [
        "The salt-pans dried out years back; only the pit-keep still holds its footing.",
        "Claim-jumpers squat the southeast bowl - break them before the tide turns and the dark comes in.",
        "Then it is brine and barnacle: hulks that chew the walls, wraiths that arc across the causeways."
      ]
    }
  ],
  "outro": [
    {
      "title": "The Pit Holds",
      "art": "dawn",
      "lines": [
        "Three nights, and the keep still stands above the dry brine.",
        "The hulks washed back out with the salt. The quarry is yours."
      ]
    }
  ],
